author: ET Online
title: An Indore physician could be the first frontline worker to die of Covid-19
description: Dr Shatrughan Panjwani, who tested positive four days ago, died in the wee hours of Thursday at city's Aurobindo Hospital. It is not clear at the moment how he contracted the virus.
content:
In what could possibly be the first casualty among frontline workers, a 62-year-old Indore physician has died because of novel coronavirus.
